page.title: 09Wild Plant Life.
page.content: The moors and forest of Fylingdales and Ugglebarnby Moors are rich in wild plant life. The moors are the home of many heathers, bracken, gorse, broom and ferns having a very heavy peaty soil. Wild plants flourish in the forest areas. The quite dark, damp area is the home of numerous wild plants including Marsh Thistle, Ragged Robin, Small hair grass, Wood Dog Violet. Bluebells, Spotted Orchid, Primrose and many varieties of ferns and bracken. The hedgerows abound in wild plant life. The common daisy, Buttercup, Clover, Foxglove and Dandelion can be seen on the grass verges whilst the hedges are host to the Wild Dog Rose, Brambles, Meadow Pea and Wild Strawberries.
